** A life of participation, opportunity, and choice. **

We believe at the core of who we are and what’s important to us, is our
people. Generous, caring, compassionate, and resilient, they embody what we do
every day. Autism affects how a person interprets the world and can cause
differences in communication and interacting with others.

Our therapy groups help provide ** a safe and inclusive space ** for autistic
people of all ages to ** explore special interests ** and ** help build their
skills. **

We are looking for mentors who have a ** high level of knowledge and
experience with digital media, creative industries and/or games development
and design ** to engage our adult and adolescent clients using their preferred
technology and their own interests.

This role will see you demonstrating various programs, technologies, games and
troubleshooting and hardware or software issues that may arise during group
sessions while supporting our coordinators and therapists in helping our
clients work towards their chosen goals.

_ “The wellbeing received from engaging in that passion and interest can
transfer into every area of life” _

** Some of the group experiences and technologies could involve; **

** **

  * Photo editing or graphic design programs 
  * Video game experience (Minecraft, RPG Maker, etc) 
  * Adobe suite including editing, sound design, animation 
  * Photography and/or short film making 
  * YouTube 
  * Dungeon Master (Dungeons and Dragons), or other tabletop RPG/strategy games 

_ _

_ We are looking for a tertiary qualification in a creative or IT related
field, or equivalent experience. _

** From health and wellness programs to professional development, we encourage our staff to strive for a better balance. **

  * Access up to $18,000 in Not-For-Profit salary packaging. 
  * Look after your health through discounts to eligible Medibank private health insurance options, with singles through to family coverage options available. 
  * Exceptional professional development opportunities to support your career growth. 
  * Prioritise wellbeing through a discounted Fitness Passport with access to various fitness and aquatic centres all around the country – for you AND your immediate family! 
  * Be part of an organisation with a practice excellence team dedicated to providing our people with clinical supervision and mentoring. 
  * You’ll have access to the latest research through our own research and development team. 
  * Gain meaningful experience through empowering autistic people, their families, carers, and the wider community. 

_ “They are determined to make a difference in the lives of their clients. And
their everyday impact is undeniable.” _

